What is StringTokenizer?
..............................
StringTokenizer is a class in the java.util package used to split a string into multiple tokens based on a delimiter.


Syntax
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(String str);

Or

StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(String str, ",");


Split by Space
import java.util.StringTokenizer;

public class Demo {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        StringTokenizer st =
                new StringTokenizer("Java Spring Boot");

        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {

            System.out.println(st.nextToken());
        }
    }
}
Output
Java
Spring
Boot


Example 2: Split by Comma
import java.util.StringTokenizer;

public class Demo {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String data = "Java,Spring,SQL,React";

        StringTokenizer st =
                new StringTokenizer(data, ",");

        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {

            System.out.println(st.nextToken());
        }
    }
}
Output
Java
Spring
SQL
React


